## Locked Design Rules (All of V2)

These apply to every new screen and component.

| Area | Rules |
|------|--------|
| **Brand & Identity** | Use original color palette only; original background imagery per page; original transparency/glass feel — refined, not exaggerated. |
| **Shape & Components** | Default radius 8px; max 12px; no pills as default; no circular avatars unless necessary; containers > cards > chips (clear hierarchy). |
| **Layout** | Mobile-first; no horizontal scrolling ever; content always visually anchored; clear separation between sections. |
| **Typography** | Strong hierarchy; labels subdued; data emphasized; no unnecessary center alignment. |
| **Motion** | Motion supports understanding; motion never distracts; respect reduced motion; performance first. |

**UX philosophy:** If it feels playful, it’s wrong. If it feels sterile, it’s wrong. If it feels **confident and calm** — it’s right.

